German[edit]

Etymology[edit]

From mit- +‎ nehmen

Pronunciation[edit]

  • Audio
    		(file)
  • Audio (Austria)
    		(file)
  • IPA(key): /ˈmɪtˌneːmən/

Verb[edit]

mitnehmen (class 4 strong, third-person singular simple present nimmt mit, past tense nahm mit, past participle mitgenommen, past subjunctive nähme mit, auxiliary haben)

  1. to carry along
  2. to pick up
  3. to take away
